2 SECTION 3. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 519 IS CREATED TO
3 READ AS FOLLOWS:
4 (1) A person is guilty of interference with a legislative proceeding in the second
5 degree when, with the intent to disrupt, impede, or prevent the General Assembly
6 from conducting business, he or she knowingly:
7 (a) Enters into or remains inside, conspires to enter into or remain inside, or
8 facilitates another person entering into or remaining inside a chamber or
9 gallery of the General Assembly, or another room inside a legislative
10 building that is set aside or designated for the use of the members of the
11 General Assembly; or
12 (b) Obstructs or impedes, conspires to obstruct or impede, or facilitates another
13 person obstructing or impeding a legislator, legislative officer, or legislative
14 staff member's ingress, egress, or movement within a legislative building.
15 (2) Interference with a legislative proceeding in the second degree is a Class B
16 misdemeanor for the first offense and a Class A misdemeanor for a second or
17 subsequent offense.
